1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:03,000
[thunder rumbling]

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:06,000
<i>[eerie music playing]</i>

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:09,000
[engine revving] [tires screeching]

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,000
-(GROANS)
-You okay?

5
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:15,000
[glass shatters] What was that?

6
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:18,000
DISPATCHER (over radio): Unit 5, respond

7
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:21,000
[in Spanish] Buenos días

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:24,000
-[clears throat]
-As I was saying...

9
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:27,000
(PHONE RINGING)
(DOOR KNOCKING)

10
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,000
[WOMAN ON TV] Today's forecast shows...

11
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:33,000
♪♪ (upbeat jazz playing)

12
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:36,000
[speaking indistinctly]

13
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:39,000
-(GASPS) Oh my God!
-(SCREAMS)

14
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,000
[ANNOUNCER] And the winner is...

15
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:45,000
<i>(wind howling)</i>
It's so cold

16
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,000
(BREATHING HEAVILY)
-Run!
-I'm trying!

17
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,000
[boy] She sleepwalks sometimes
since our parents died.

18
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,000
-Nobody, that's who. [chuckles]
-["My Favourite Game" playing on stereo]

19
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:57,000
-First person speaking
-Second person responds
-Third person adds comment
